  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Developing the App Concept**\n\nI\'m focusing on user input. I\'ll need to allow users to specify image settings, post type (Reel, Story, Feed), aesthetic style, and desired color palettes. My goal is to automatically generate the correct output sizes for Instagram and TikTok. I am now considering book colors to use as a focus.\n\n\n**Clarifying Brand Requirements**\n\nI\'m now clarifying branding requirements. The user\'s instructions seem contradictory regarding the gold foil monogram\'s placement. I need to resolve this discrepancy before proceeding. I\'m focusing on reconciling the initial requests with the detailed brand guide. Let me make sure the prompt generator is able to resolve the issue.\n\n\n**Defining Interactive Tools**\n\nI\'m now thinking about the interactive configuration tool and web application components. I want to include an AI image generator or prompt compiler. The goal is to allow users to specify image settings, post types, aesthetics, book cover colors and textures, and the state of the book. I plan to handle aspect ratios automatically. The user will be able to select various content details.\n\n\n**Exploring Image Generation Options**\n\nI\'m now investigating image generation options and prompt detail. Can I use the Gemini API to generate the image itself? It appears I can use `gemini-api` to generate both detailed prompts and maybe call an image generation API, or even use Gemini 2.0 and Imagen to generate previews. First, I want to confirm our skill access. I\'m focusing on the prompt generation details.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now inspect the `gemini-api` and `image-generation` skills to ensure that we implement the prompt engineering engine and image preview capabilities in compliance with modern guidelines."
