    thinking: "**Addressing Transient Errors**\n\nI\'m currently encountering transient RPC errors and timeouts. My initial instinct is to try simple debugging steps like running a grep command, attempting a compilation, or restarting the dev server. I also considered waiting, but I think that I can modify the code directly, since I have the key file contents and initial file tree. Now, I\'m reviewing the prompt to clarify the goal.\n\n\n**Defining Content Specifications**\n\nI\'m now focusing on user input parameters for automated content creation. I\'ve broken down the inputs into an image setting description, post type (Instagram Post, Story, Reel), aesthetic style, and book color/swatch (Ink, Echo, Haze, or Parchment). I will also gather further details, asking if the book is open, the cover texture (Linen or Leather), interior spread topic (if open), internal photo color scheme, and workspace surface type.\n\n\n**Specifying Output Requirements**\n\nI\'m now diving into the specifics of output generation. I\'ve defined aspect ratios for various Instagram formats (Post, Story, Reel). My focus is on the prompt engineering engine, which I\'m designing to translate creative concepts into detailed prompts. I\'ve decided to leverage a server-side Gemini call via `/api/generate-content-prompt` for prompt generation using Gemini 3.5 Flash. I\'m also considering image generation capabilities, potentially using `gemini-2.5-flash-image`.\n\n\n**Visualizing Detailed Workspace**\n\nI\'m now generating specific workspace details for the \"Vellum & Vestige\" Brand Studio. I\'ve designed a visual form to customize monograph visuals, including Instagram formats (Square, Portrait, Story, Reel). I\'m focusing on book states (closed or open spread), and key brand colors (Ink, Echo, Haze, Parchment). Furthermore, I\'ve specified cover textures (linen, leather), workspace surfaces (concrete, slate, linen sheet), and interior spread topics and photo tones for open spreads.\n\n\n**Refining Image Generation**\n\nI\'m now refining the image generation workflow. I\'ve broken it down into a sequence triggered by a \"Generate Prompt & Preview\" click. I\'m focusing on the server-side API calls. The first call to `/api/generate-prompt` crafts a detailed prompt, and the second to `/api/generate-image` will trigger image generation, both using the Gemini models. The initial image prompt will include branding details, such as light casting and logo stamps.\n\n\n**Confirming Engine Implementation**\n\nNow I\'m focusing on the implementation details for image generation, specifically confirming how to use the Gemini API. I verified I can leverage `gemini-2.5-flash-image` on the server-side, but I\'m pausing to consider user choice or a toggle between this and standard image generation for different results. However, the existing prompt reminds me to craft prompts that align perfectly with the Master Brand Guide, so I\'ll output image prompts immediately. I will include a markdown code block with the final optimized image prompt and a bulleted confirmation ledger of the Swatch, Orientation/Aspect Ratio, and State.\n\n\n"
