  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Content Parameters**\n\nI\'m currently focused on defining the initial parameters for content creation. The user will specify the image setting, using either a custom description of the environment or pre-set options. Additionally, I need to nail down the type of post: Instagram post dimensions (square 1:1, portrait 4:5), or Instagram Story (9:16). This initial data drives all of the following stages.\n\n\n**Expanding Aesthetic Specifications**\n\nI\'m now expanding the aesthetic style options; this includes the \"Vellum & Vestige Art Director\" tool\'s book attributes. I\'m focusing on defining specific book colors, cover materials, and whether the book is open or closed, which will drive image generation. Also, I\'m considering other helpful prompts like photography angle and style that affect the image.\n\n\n**Refining Branding Consistency**\n\nI\'m now integrating brand guidelines for gold foil embossing and monogram placement, resolving the apparent conflict between user input and the Brand Guide\'s rules. I\'m focusing on allowing customization while maintaining brand consistency. I\'m considering using Gemini to refine prompts for sophisticated imagery and to generate visual mockups.\n\n\n**Analyzing Gemini Integration**\n\nI\'m now analyzing the feasibility of integrating Google\'s Gemini model directly within the front-end. I\'m focusing on evaluating client-side implementations using the `@google/genai` package. I\'m checking for environment variable availability, considering proxy methods, or exploring standard prompt engineering techniques. The goal is seamless and efficient image prompt refinement.\n\n\n**Implementing Prompt Directives**\n\nI\'m now implementing the core prompt logic within a React state machine, focusing on automatic compilation and refinement based on structured directives. I\'m prioritizing adherence to the specific prompt rules, particularly Section IV, which dictates the output format: a single markdown code block with the optimized image prompt, followed by a 3-bullet confirmation ledger for Swatch, Orientation/Aspect Ratio, and State. My aim is to deliver a highly professional UI for an \"Editorial Aesthetic\" experience with dual modes.\n\n\n**Developing Interactive Mockups**\n\nI\'m now focusing on a new real-time mockup of the book, dynamically showcasing selected swatches, cover textures via SVGs/CSS, and gold foil monograms. The interactive 3D rendering will feature custom book states, allowing me to view a closed monograph or an open spread with customized scenes, all to refine prompt generation. I\'m also planning a smart prompt generator that compiles raw user concepts into the exact \"Vellum & Vestige\" prompt structure via a styled text interface.\n\n\n**Developing Brand Guideline Panel**\n\nI\'m now designing an \"Editorial Aesthetic\" brand guideline panel as an elegant drawer. I\'m focusing on incorporating a styled text interface for \"Vellum & Vestige\" guardrails, including the 12\"x9\" ratio, authorized swatches, gold foil stamps, daylight shadow, and minimalist concrete workspace. I\'m also planning to create an exact SVG monogram from the logo and render the \"VV\" lettering in gold foil using CSS gradients and shadow effects. Finally, I\'m integrating the specified swatches and material descriptions into the interface.\n\n\n**Refining Interface Controls**\n\nI\'m now focusing on a new highly interactive React application, designing real-time controls and perfect state alignment. The elegant prompt compiler is shaping up, automatically crafting detailed prompts following Vellum & Vestige\'s strict rules, complete with an intuitive input field for scene context, aesthetic styles, subject, and custom refinements. I\'m also planning the design of a \"Refined Prompt\" output area, styled like a high-end editorial display. I\'m prioritizing the 12\"x9\" book ratio, upper-third logo embossing with gold foil, morning sunlight with defined geometric shadows, and a minimalist concrete workspace.\n\n\n**Enhancing Mockup Features**\n\nI\'m now integrating dynamic 3D shadows and texture toggles for linen and leather, using SVGs and gradients. I\'m also planning an open spread page display with curated photos to show heartwarming moments with directional sunlight overlays. Furthermore, I\'m working to integrate a \"Copy Prompt\" button and a brand compliance indicator into the publication block. I\'m also investigating Gemini for auto-enhancing scene contexts.\n\n\n**Designing Robust Compilation**\n\nI\'m now focusing on developing a comprehensive client-side template compiler. It will instantly generate the exact markdown prompt block, along with an optional \"Ask Gemini to refine scene\" button, using standard `@google/genai` or a client-side API call. I\'m also planning a robust fallback to an offline prompt compiler if an API key is unavailable. It should include an offline automatic generator with a beautiful Gemini prompt enhancer. My goal is 100% reliability and a stunning \"Editorial Aesthetic\" design. I will start by writing a polished `App.tsx` and check the design\'s HTML code to adopt the precise fonts, colors, spacing, borders, and shadows.\n\n\n\n**Crafting UI Elements**\n\nI\'m now crafting the UI elements with a focus on an elegant SVG-based monogram. I\'m prioritizing a high-end calligraphic \"VV\" monogram by extracting or designing incredibly artistic paths. I\'m focusing on responsiveness and beautiful layout, using CSS to incorporate color accents and fonts. This includes designing a container and a corresponding SVG path. I\'m also planning to build a magnificent and responsive UI container.\n\n\n**Refining Monogram Design**\n\nI\'m now iterating on the SVG monogram, focusing on refining the calligraphic \"VV\" paths for a beautiful, organic serif look. I\'m focusing on responsiveness and visual elegance with CSS color accents and fonts. The goal is a high-end monogram for the interface.\n\n\n\n**Defining Dashboard Details**\n\nI\'m now focusing on defining the dashboard\'s details. I\'m working on the core file `/src/App.tsx`, and making sure I understand the exact inputs the user will provide. I\'m prioritizing user input clarity for Scene Context, Post Type, Aesthetic Style, and Book specifications to ensure a streamlined user experience. This includes specific book colors and open/closed states. I\'ll focus on an elegant SVG monogram for the UI.\n\n\n**Implementing Feature Toggles**\n\nI\'m now implementing the feature toggle for logo placement, carefully balancing brand guidelines and user requests. I\'m focusing on providing users a choice between the classic upper-third brand-standard placement and a customized bottom-centered option, using an intuitive UI switch. This feature highlights responsiveness to both the rules and the user\'s instructions.\n\n\n**Developing Component UI**\n\nI\'m now focusing on developing a React component to meet the specifications, using `lucide-react` icons and `framer-motion` animations. I\'m focusing on creating an \"Editorial Aesthetic\" mockup with real-time controls, prompt generation, and responsive design, while ensuring the project is error-free, and I am confident that all dependencies are correct. I\'m prioritizing user experience and a seamless design.\n\n\n"
