  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Volume Selection**\n\nI\'m currently focused on how to let the user select the volume they want to work with. I think keeping the options to volumes I, II, III, or IV is a good plan for simplicity. I\'m prioritizing user control and easy navigation through the system, considering the \'Provenance\' of Volume I as a starting point.\n\n\n**Updating Volume Selection**\n\nI\'ve formalized the volume options into a `VOLUMES` list with IDs, labels, and titles. I\'ve also implemented a `selectedVolume` state variable in the `App` component to handle user selection. This will allow for easier navigation through the different volumes and their associated content. The previous code didn\'t have this, so it needed to be added to reflect the desired state. Also I\'m working on the design elements of the prompt.\n\n\n**Reviewing Cover Design Elements**\n\nI\'m now diving into the specifics of the book cover layout, referencing images for accuracy. I\'m focusing on incorporating elements like centered gold-embossed text (e.g., \"Volume II: The Ascent\") in the upper/middle section, and the centered \"VV\" monogram (gold-embossed/foil-stamped) near the bottom. I\'m also including \"VELLUM & VESTIGE\" text and planning for configurable options to match the real cover exactly. The goal is a faithful representation. I am currently reading the prompt generation code.\n\n\n**Refining Cover Layout**\n\nI\'m now integrating volume-specific titles into the cover layout, ensuring they match the provided images. The focus is on implementing centered, gold-embossed text with the correct volume title for each. I\'m also addressing the `VV` monogram and its optional sub-text, and verifying the prompt generation in `getCompiledPrompt()` to accurately reflect these design elements. The images are my guide!\n\n\n**Adjusting Prompt Generation**\n\nI\'m now revising the prompt generation in `getCompiledPrompt()` to explicitly control the text for the \"closed\" state cover