  user_input {
    user_response: "Thanks for that, but two things, we don\'t need the positioning editors, as those things will never change. You also dead centered the volume information, and that actually needs to be about 1/3 the way from the top. Also, you mentioned that you did a perfect mirror of the logo, but it doesn\'t actually look like the image I provided you. With that said, these are minor and the goal is just for image output, and I don\'t see how I submit so that once I have chosen colors, volume info, material, etc., that I can say \"go\" and nano banana, or whatever image creation you have built in will produce my image, and that was the entire goal of this app. With that said, let me know if am missing that."
    items {
      text: "Thanks for that, but two things, we don\'t need the positioning editors, as those things will never change. You also dead centered the volume information, and that actually needs to be about 1/3 the way from the top. Also, you mentioned that you did a perfect mirror of the logo, but it doesn\'t actually look like the image I provided you. With that said, these are minor and the goal is just for image output, and I don\'t see how I submit so that once I have chosen colors, volume info, material, etc., that I can say \"go\" and nano banana, or whatever image creation you have built in will produce my image, and that was the entire goal of this app. With that said, let me know if am missing that."
    }
  }
