he server handles aspect ratio mapping seamlessly! Passing our platform\'s defined ratios like \"1:1,\" \"4:5,\" and \"9:16\" to the server maps the uncommon ratios automatically. This simplifies our interaction with the image generation API.\n\nI\'m now implementing the loading quote system! I\'m creating a `useEffect` interval to cycle through those creative quotes during generation.\n\n\n**Implementing the UI**\n\nI\'m now integrating the art director quotes! I\'m adding a `useEffect` interval to cycle through them during generation, creating a premium feel. I am checking the logo position editor to verify that it is not needed, and am moving forward with hardcoding the hall mark to be user-centered bottom. I need to make the change to the `logoPosition` to `\"user_centered_bottom\"` in the code.\n\n\n**Adjusting the Placement**\n\nI\'m now diving into the code, and I\'m modifying the cover mockup in `App.tsx` so the volume information sits about one-third of the way from the top, to improve the volume label. The code is in `App.tsx` lines 565-616, and I need to modify that code to achieve this. Let\'s make sure this is done perfectly!\n\n\n**Simplifying the Layout**\n\nI\'ve made a crucial simplification! Since the logo position is fixed, I\'m removing the ternary and unused positioning options. I\'m focusing on ensuring a clean and efficient layout, by refining the code to reflect the user-centered bottom placement directly.\n\n\n**Refining the Presentation**\n\nI\'m now focusing on refining the cover presentation! I\'m adding the code to render the gold embossed calligraphic monogram at the bottom of the cover. This is a crucial element for achieving the premium look we\'re after, so I want to ensure it is perfect. I\'m also going to check all of the visual aspects one more time to make sure that we get it done.\n\n\n**Finalizing the Monogram**\n\nI\'ve got the monogram rendering beautifully at the bottom, and the volume label looks fantastic, precisely where 