  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing the App**\n\nI\'m structuring the rendering flow in `/src/App.tsx`. I\'m focusing on the center area, which will dynamically render based on `viewMode`, showing either \"draft\" or \"photo.\" The layout design is within `Preview Canvas`.\n\n\n**Refining the Mode Selector**\n\nI\'ve been working on the mode selector tabs within the `Preview Canvas`. I\'m using a `div` for layout, with buttons for \"draft\" and \"photo\" modes. The `viewMode` state determines which button has the \"active\" styling, which is designed to provide visual feedback to the user. I\'ve styled the active state with a background color, text color, and shadow. I\'m also ensuring the visual design is appealing.\n\n\n**Implementing the \"Photo\" Mode**\n\nI\'m working on the AI photorealism button in \"photo\" mode. I\'ve styled the button with a background, text, shadow, and transition for visual feedback when it\'s active. The `Sparkles` icon is in the button, and I\'ve integrated a conditional check with `isGenerating` to trigger `handleGenerateImage()` when this button is clicked.\n\n\n**Analyzing Visual Directives**\n\nI\'m focused on incorporating the \"Visual Director Notes\" to enhance realism. I\'m prioritizing the gold foil stamp\'s response to lighting. I also need to ensure the edge material has an authentic layered feel. The mockups are coming together nicely. I am currently working on the \"draft\" view.\n\n\n**Styling the \"Draft\" View**\n\nI\'m focused on the visual style for the \"draft\" view. I\'m experimenting with a layered aesthetic for the canvas. I\'ve been implementing the background color from SWATCHES based on the swatch ID and applying a box shadow for depth. I\'m also adding a spine detail effect using gradients and borders to simulate an edge. I\'m using linen texture to enhance the feel.\n\n\n**Simulating Sunlight Effects**\n\nI\'m now incorporating simulated lighting effects within the \"draft\" view. I\'m experimenting with a soft light overlay using radial gradients to give a subtle texture. I\'m also implementing directional sunlight simulation, with a white/transparent gradient for a realistic effect. I\'m using a series title placement about a third of the way down to finish things off.\n\n\n**Refining Text Elements**\n\nI\'m currently working on enhancing the visual presentation of text elements within the UI. I\'m focusing on the volume label and title, experimenting with font weights, sizes, and drop shadows to ensure readability and aesthetic appeal. I\'ve integrated a background gradient for the title, aiming for a subtle yet impactful effect. I\'m adding a divider to separate title from other elements, and animating the monogram for a more engaging look.\n\n\n**Enhancing the UI**\n\nI\'m focused on the VV monogram and title presentation. I\'m working with a serif font, italic style, and gradient background for the monogram, adding a drop shadow for depth. I\'m also implementing a gradient background and a divider for the title, along with a custom font and tracking to enhance the visual appeal. I want to make sure the presentation is aesthetically pleasing.\n\n\n**Developing the Fold Detail**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the center fold detail. I\'m adding a shadow effect using a gradient, and positioning it precisely to give a realistic impression of a fold. I\'m also working on the left page texture, making it appear thick. I\'ve added a soft, subtle overlay to enhance depth. I\'m placing an element in the corner for a visual break. I\'ve also added a small element in the corner for visual depth and break.\n\n\n**Implementing the Right Page**\n\nI\'m now implementing the right page with its heartwarming editorial photo. I\'ve set the background to a light beige and added an overlay for depth. I\'m focusing on the styled photo frame with border and texture, and I\'m using a mix-blend-multiply effect for the overlay to enhance the visual integration.\n\n\n**Refining Overlay Effects**\n\nI\'m now refining the overlay effects on the right page\'s photo. I\'m focusing on the `mix-blend-multiply` effect. I\'m experimenting with a \"sunray\" overlay using a gradient to create a warm, natural lighting effect, adding a subtle blur for realism. I\'m also implementing styles.\n\n\n**Finalizing Aesthetics**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the final aesthetic details of the photo view. I\'ve added a themed text with a brief description beneath the image. I\'ve also integrated the Hasselblad camera stamp in the bottom right corner, as well as final series labels, including sensitive series. I\'m aiming for a sophisticated final look.\n\n\n**Adding Final Text Details**\n\nI\'m now integrating the final text elements. I\'m focusing on the \"Open cotton spread\" text, adjusting font size, tracking, and color for a balanced presentation. I\'ve also implemented the dynamic trigger button, ensuring it triggers image generation as expected. I\'m pleased with the current aesthetics.\n\n\n**Iterating on Button Styles**\n\nI\'m currently focused on the design of the image generation button in the photo mode. I\'m refining the styles for the visual feedback, adding a `transition-all` effect on hover, and working on the `Generate Photorealistic Art` button. I\'m also ensuring the text is readable by adjusting font size, tracking, and color to achieve a balanced look.\n\n\n**Refining Generation Feedback**\n\nI\'m now iterating on the generation feedback elements. I\'m styling a loading animation with a spinning circle and loading text updates using quotes. I\'m adding a \"Generating...\" title, updating the quote index, and a subtle divider. I\'m also including the engaged model. I\'m trying to balance visual engagement and informative clarity for the user.\n\n\n**Addressing Generation Errors**\n\nI\'m now implementing the error state UI for image generation. I\'ve designed a centered modal with a red-themed visual to indicate a refusal. I\'ve included a help circle icon, a title \"Generation Refused\", and a user-friendly error message within the modal. I\'ve incorporated \"Retry\" and \"Go Back\" buttons.\n\n\n**Adjusting Feedback Elements**\n\nI\'m now revising the feedback elements within the UI. I\'m focusing on the \"Back to Draft\" button in the photo view, refining its styling. I\'m also ensuring visual consistency, with an updated look that features a rounded shape, a subtle shadow, and an updated background color. The text now has bold styling for better visibility.\n\n\n**Finalizing Download Integration**\n\nI\'m now integrating the download functionality for the generated image. I\'ve added a download button in the photo mode. The download feature retrieves the `generatedImageUrl` for the download, using the `selectedVolume` for naming. The download also includes styles to enhance the user experience.\n\n\n\n**Refining Final Callouts**\n\nI\'m now integrating the final visual callouts. I\'ve designed a centered callout with a theme and a brief, descriptive quote beneath the image. I\'ve also added a \'Modify Settings\' button, and a supporting disclaimer. I\'m aiming for a clear and helpful user experience.\n\n\n\n**Finalizing Callout Refinement**\n\nI\'m making final tweaks to the recent visual additions, ensuring the balance between the elements. I\'m focusing on text placement to ensure everything is readable, and I\'m finalizing callout placement. I\'m prioritizing overall aesthetic harmony.\n\n\n**Adjusting Image Download**\n\nI\'m now revising the image download feature. I\'ve streamlined the process to use `downloadGeneratedImage()` within a `useEffect` hook, triggered by the `generatedImageUrl` state. I\'ve also incorporated a `try...catch` block to handle potential errors during the download process for more robust handling.\n\n\n\n"
